{{Nihongo|'''''Extermination of Evil'''''|è¾éªçµµ|Hekija-E}} is a set of five paintings depicting [[List of Asian mythologies|traditional Asian deities]] banishing evil. The paintings are collectively listed as a [[List of National Treasures of Japan (paintings)|National Treasure of Japan]] and held at the [[Nara National Museum]].

==Overview==
The paintings are thought to have been created during the 12th century, during the reign of [[Emperor Go-Shirakawa]] in the [[Heian period]];{{sfn|e-Museum, Extermination of Evil}} they may have also been produced during the Kamakura period.{{sfn|Bunka.nii.ac.jp, ç´æ¬èè²è¾éªçµµ}} The [[Japanese calligraphy|calligrapher]] is thought to be the same on the five scrolls as on the [[Hell Scroll (Tokyo National Museum)|Hell Scroll]] and the Demon of Punishment,{{sfn|e-Museum, Extermination of Evil}} which were produced at roughly the same time.{{sfn|Bunka.nii.ac.jp, ç´æ¬èè²è¾éªçµµ}} They are thought to have originally been a single handscroll,{{sfn|e-Museum, Extermination of Evil}}{{sfn|Bunka.nii.ac.jp, ç´æ¬èè²è¾éªçµµ}} known as the "second edition of the Masuda family Hell Scroll", that was stored in the RengeÅ-in Temple (now [[SanjÅ«sangen-dÅ]]). The paintings depict five benevolent deities in combat against evil, as represented by demons; the deities come from several cultures, including contemporary [[Japanese culture|Japanese]], [[Chinese culture|Chinese]], and [[Indian culture|Indian]]. They are thought to be associated with the Hell Transformation Screens then used in [[Nara Prefecture|Nara]] for repentance ceremonies at the end of each year, where the devout recited the names of the buddhas at [[HeijÅ Palace]].{{sfn|e-Museum, Extermination of Evil}}

The paintings were designated National Treasures of Japan on 6 June 1985,{{sfn|Bunka.nii.ac.jp, ç´æ¬èè²è¾éªçµµ}} with the [[Accession number (library science)|accession number]] 1106.{{sfn|e-Museum, Extermination of Evil}} They are located at the [[Nara National Museum]] in [[Nara, Nara|Nara]], [[Nara Prefecture]].{{sfn|Nara, Extermination of Evil}}

