===Tenkeisei===
[[File:Extermination of Evil Tenkeisei.jpg|300px|left|thumb|Tenkeisei]]
Tenkeisei (å¤©åæ, literally meaning "the star [that metes out] heavenly punishment"), or the God of Heavenly Punishment, is a deity from the Chinese tradition of [[yin and yang]]. Originally a demon, he later took on a role in [[Vajrayana]] prayers. In the painting he is depicted fighting and consuming [[Ox-Head and Horse-Face|Gozu TennÃ´]], an ox-headed deity worshipped at the [[Yasaka Shrine|Gion Shrine]] (present day Yasaka) in [[Kyoto]].{{sfn|e-Museum, Extermination of Evil}} The painting measures {{convert|26|by|39.2|cm|in}} and has the accession number 1106-1.{{sfn|Nara, Tenkeisei, God}}
