===Bishamon Ten===
[[File:Extermination of Evil Vaisravana.jpg|300px|thumb|left|[[VaiÅravaá¹a|Bishamonten]]]]
Bishamonten (æ¯æ²éå¤©) is the Japanese name for [[VaiÅravaá¹a]], the chief of the [[Four Heavenly Kings]]. In the image, he is depicted protecting followers of the [[Lotus Sutra]] from evil while carrying a bow. His equipment is similar to that found in Chinese paintings from the [[Tang Dynasty|Tang]] and [[Song Dynasty|Song]] dynasties.{{sfn|e-Museum, Extermination of Evil}} The painting measures {{convert|25.8|by|76.5|cm|in}} and has the accession number 1106-5.{{sfn|Nara, Bishamon Ten}} 
